Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper deals with the Elliptic Curve Discrete Logarithm Problem (EC-DLP) which is a fundamental problem in cryptography. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of Summation Polynomials and Weil Descent algorithms which are related to coding theory and information theory. 
3. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the time complexity of the algorithms used to solve the EC-DLP problem. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the use of F4 (Faugere) algorithms to solve the over-determined system of equations arising from the EC-DLP problem. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the use of quantum algorithms to expedite the process of solving the over-determined system of equations arising from the EC-DLP problem.
